Agra Fort.label: Agra Fort
Agra Fort.description: Agra Fort, is a monument, a UNESCO World Heritage site located in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. It is about 2.5 km northwest of its more famous sister monument, the Taj Mahal. The fort can be more accurately described as a walled city. Wikipedia

Aït Benhaddou.label: Aït Benhaddou
Aït Benhaddou.description: Aït Benhaddou is a fortified city, or ksar, along the former caravan route between the Sahara and Marrakech in present-day Morocco. Wikipedia

Albula Railway.label: Albula Railway
Albula Railway.description: The Albula Railway is a single track metre gauge railway line forming part of the so-called core network of the Rhaetian Railway, in the Canton of Graubünden, Switzerland. Wikipedia

Alcobaça Monastery.label: Alcobaça Monastery
Alcobaça Monastery.description: The Alcobaça Monastery is a Mediaeval Roman Catholic Monastery located in the town of Alcobaça, in central Portugal. Wikipedia

Bahla Fort.label: Bahla Fort
Bahla Fort.description: Bahla Fort is one of four historic fortresses situated at the foot of the Djebel Akhdar highlands in Oman. It was built in the 13th and 14th centuries, when the oasis of Bahla was prosperous under the control of the Banu Nabhan tribe. Wikipedia

Amalfi Coast.label: Amalfi Coast
Amalfi Coast.description: The Amalfi Coast is a stretch of coastline on the southern coast of the Sorrentine Peninsula in the Province of Salerno in Southern Italy. Wikipedia

Ban Chiang.label: Ban Chiang
Ban Chiang.description: Ban Chiang is an archeological site located in Nong Han district, Udon Thani Province, Thailand. It has been on the UNESCO world heritage list since 1992. Wikipedia

Bremen Roland.label: Bremen Roland
Bremen Roland.description: The Bremen Roland is a statue of Roland, erected in 1404. It stands in the market square of Bremen, Germany, facing the cathedral, and shows Roland, paladin of the first Holy Roman Emperor Charlemagne and hero of the Battle of Roncevaux Pass. Wikipedia

Central Suriname Nature Reserve.label: Central Suriname Nature Reserve
Central Suriname Nature Reserve.description: The Central Suriname Nature Reserve was created in 1998 by Conservation International and the government of Suriname. Wikipedia

Cathedral of Trier.label: Cathedral of Trier
Cathedral of Trier.description: The High Cathedral of Saint Peter in Trier is a Roman Catholic church in Trier, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. It is the oldest cathedral in the country. Wikipedia

Chavín de Huantar.label: Chavín de Huantar
Chavín de Huantar.description: Chavín de Huántar is an archaeological site containing ruins and artifacts constructed beginning at least by 1200 BCE and occupied by later cultures until around 400-500 BCE by the Chavín, a major pre-Inca culture. Wikipedia

Certosa di Padula.label: Certosa di Padula
Certosa di Padula.description: Padula Charterhouse, in Italian Certosa di Padula, is a large Carthusian monastery, or charterhouse, located in the town of Padula, in the Cilento National Park in Southern Italy. It is a World Heritage site. Wikipedia

Complex of Goguryeo Tombs.label: Complex of Goguryeo Tombs
Complex of Goguryeo Tombs.description: The Complex of Goguryeo Tombs lie in North Korea. In July 2004, they became the first UNESCO World Heritage site in the country. Wikipedia

Churches of Chiloé.label: Churches of Chiloé
Churches of Chiloé.description: The Churches of Chiloé in Chile's Chiloé Archipelago are a unique architectural phenomenon in the Americas, and one of the most prominent styles of Chilota architecture. Wikipedia

Copán.label: Copán
Copán.description: Copán is an archaeological site of the Maya civilization located in the Copán Department of western Honduras, not far from the border with Guatemala. It was the capital city of a major Classic period kingdom from the 5th to 9th centuries AD. Wikipedia

El Vizcaíno Biosphere Reserve.label: El Vizcaíno Biosphere Reserve
El Vizcaíno Biosphere Reserve.description: The El Vizcaíno Biosphere Reserve, created in 1988, is located in Mulegé Municipality in northern Baja California Sur, at the center of the Baja California Peninsula between the Pacific Ocean and Sea of Cortez. Wikipedia

Djémila.label: Djémila
Djémila.description: Djémila is a mountain village in Algeria, near the northern coast east of Algiers, where some of the best preserved Berbero-Roman ruins in North Africa are found. It is situated in the region bordering the Constantinois and Petite Kabylie. Wikipedia

Engelsberg Ironworks.label: Engelsberg Ironworks
Engelsberg Ironworks.description: Engelsberg Ironworks is an ironworks in Ängelsberg, a village in Fagersta Municipality in Västmanland, Sweden. It was built in 1681 by Per Larsson Gyllenhöök and developed into one of the world's most modern ironworks in the period 1700-1800. Wikipedia

East Rennell.label: East Rennell
East Rennell.description: East Rennell is the southern portion of Rennell Island in the Solomon Islands which is designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Wikipedia

Gorée.label: Gorée
Gorée.description:
Île de Gorée at sea from the main harbor of Dakar (14°40′0″N 17°24′0″W﻿ / ﻿14.66667°N 17.40000°W).
Its population as of 31 January 2005 official estimates is 1,056 inhabitants, giving ... Wikipedia

Frankincense Trail.label: Frankincense Trail
Frankincense Trail.description: The Frankincense Trail is a site in Oman on the Incense Road. The site includes frankincense trees, Khor Rori and the remains of a caravan oasis, which were crucial to the medieval incense trade. Wikipedia

Gough Island.label: Gough Island
Gough Island.description: Gough Island, also known historically as Gonçalo Álvares or mistakenly as Diego Alvarez, is a volcanic island in the South Atlantic Ocean. Wikipedia

Great Living Chola Temples.label: Great Living Chola Temples
Great Living Chola Temples.description: The Great Living Chola Temples are temples built during the Chola rule in the south of India. These temples are the Brihadisvara Temple at Thanjavur, the Temple of Gangaikondacholisvaram and the Airavatesvara Temple at Darasuram. Wikipedia

Hospicio Cabañas.label: Hospicio Cabañas
Hospicio Cabañas.description: The Hospicio Cabañas in Guadalajara, Jalisco, Mexico, a World Heritage Site, is one of the oldest and largest hospital complexes in the Americas. Wikipedia

Henderson Island (Pitcairn Islands).label: Henderson Island
Henderson Island (Pitcairn Islands).description: Henderson Island is an uninhabited raised coral atoll in the south Pacific Ocean. It is one of the few atolls whose ecosystems have been relatively unaffected by human contact. Wikipedia

Great Copper Mountain.label: Great Copper Mountain
Great Copper Mountain.description: Great Copper Mountain was a mine in Falun, Sweden, that operated for a millennium from the 10th century to 1992. It produced as much as two thirds of Europe's copper needs and helped fund many of Sweden's wars in the 17th century. Wikipedia

Hwaseong Fortress.label: Hwaseong Fortress
Hwaseong Fortress.description: Hwaseong is the wall surrounding the centre of Suwon, the provincial capital of Gyeonggi-do, South Korea. Wikipedia

Humberstone and Santa Laura Saltpeter Wo.label: Humberstone and Santa Laura Saltpeter Works
Humberstone and Santa Laura Saltpeter Wo.description: Humberstone and Santa Laura Saltpeter Works are two former saltpeter refineries located in northern Chile. They were declared a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2005. Wikipedia

Imperial Tombs of the Ming and Qing Dyna.label: Imperial Tombs of the Ming and Qing Dynasties
Imperial Tombs of the Ming and Qing Dyna.description: Imperial Tombs of the Ming and Qing Dynasties is the designation under which the UNESCO has included several tombs and burial complexes into the list of World Heritage Sites. These tombs date from the Ming and Qing dynasties of China. Wikipedia

Huanglong, Sichuan.label: Huanglong, Sichuan
Huanglong, Sichuan.description: Huanglong is a scenic and historic interest area in the northwest part of Sichuan, China. It is located in the southern part of the Minshan mountain range, 150 kilometres north-northwest of the capital Chengdu. Wikipedia

Incense Route – Desert Cities in the Neg.label: Negev incense route
Incense Route – Desert Cities in the Neg.description: Negev incense route is a World Heritage-designated route in the Negev, southern Israel proclaimed of outstanding universal value by UNESCO in 2005. Wikipedia

Itsukushima Shrine.label: Itsukushima Shrine
Itsukushima Shrine.description: Itsukushima Shrine is a Shinto shrine on the island of Itsukushima, best known for its "floating" torii gate. It is in the city of Hatsukaichi in Hiroshima Prefecture in Japan. Wikipedia

Jungfrau-Aletsch protected area.label: Jungfrau-Aletsch protected area
Jungfrau-Aletsch protected area.description: The Jungfrau-Aletsch protected area is located in south-western Switzerland between the cantons of Berne and Valais. Wikipedia

Kathmandu Valley.label: Kathmandu Valley
Kathmandu Valley.description: The Kathmandu Valley, located in Nepal, lies at the crossroads of ancient civilizations of Asia, and has at least 130 important monuments, including several pilgrimage sites for Hindus and Buddhists. Wikipedia

Khirokitia.label: Khirokitia
Khirokitia.description: Khirokitia is an archaeological site on the island of Cyprus dating from the Neolithic age. It has been listed as a World Heritage Site by UNESCO since 1998. Wikipedia

Koutammakou.label: KoutammakouKoutammakou
Koutammakou.description: Koutammouko, the Land of the Batammariba is a cultural landscape designated as a UNESCO World Heritage Site in northern Togo. The area features traditional mud tower-houses which remain the preferred style of living. Wikipedia

Laponian area.label: Laponian area
Laponian area.description: The Laponian area is a large mountainous wildlife area in the Lapland province in Northern Sweden, more precisely in the Gällivare Municipality, Arjeplog Municipality and Jokkmokk Municipality. Wikipedia

Kolomenskoye.label: Kolomenskoye
Kolomenskoye.description: Kolomenskoye is a former royal estate situated several kilometers to the southeast of the city center of Moscow, Russia, on the ancient road leading to the town of Kolomna. The 390 hectare scenic area overlooks the steep banks of the Moskva River. Wikipedia

Lutherhaus.label: Lutherhaus
Lutherhaus.description: The Lutherhaus in Lutherstadt Wittenberg, begun in 1504 as part of the University of Wittenberg, was the home of Martin Luther for most of his adult life and a significant location in the history of the Protestant Reformation. Wikipedia

Longmen Grottoes.label: Longmen Grottoes
Longmen Grottoes.description: The Longmen Grottoes or Longmen Caves are one of the finest examples of Chinese Buddhist art. Housing tens of thousands of statues of Buddha and his disciples, they are located 12 kilometres south of ... Wikipedia

Mana Pools.label: Mana Pools
Mana Pools.description: Mana Pools is a wildlife conservation area in northern Zimbabwe constituting a National Park. It is a region of the lower Zambezi River in Zimbabwe where the flood plain turns into a broad expanse of lakes after each rainy season. Wikipedia

Makli Hill.label: Makli Hill
Makli Hill.description: Makli Hill is one of the largest necropolises in the world, with a diameter of approximately 8 km. It lies approx. 98 km east of Karachi and is the burial place of some 125,000 local rulers, Sufi saints and others. Wikipedia

Master of the Nets Garden.label: Master of the Nets Garden
Master of the Nets Garden.description: The Master of the Nets Garden in Suzhou is among the finest gardens in China. It is located at Gusu District, Dai Cheng Qiao Road, No. 11 Kuo Jia Tou Xiang. It is recognized with other classical Suzhou gardens as a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Wikipedia

Mount Kōya.label: Mount Kōya
Mount Kōya.description: Mount Kōya is the name of mountains in Wakayama Prefecture to the south of Osaka. Also, Kōya-san is a modifying word for Kongōbu-ji. There is no one mountain officially called Kōya-san in Japan. Wikipedia

Mount Qingcheng.label: Mount Qingcheng
Mount Qingcheng.description: Mount Qingcheng is a mountain in Dujiangyan, Sichuan, China. It is amongst the most important centres of Taoism in China. In Taoism mythology, it was the site of the Yellow Emperor's studies with Ning Fengzhi. Wikipedia

Mount Emei.label: Mount Emei
Mount Emei.description: Mount Emei is a mountain in Sichuan province, China. Its name is usually written as "峨眉山" and occasionally "峩嵋山" or "峩眉山" but all three are translated as Mount Emei or Mount Emeishan. Wikipedia

Monte Albán.label: Monte Albán
Monte Albán.description: Monte Albán is a large pre-Columbian archaeological site in the Santa Cruz Xoxocotlán Municipality in the southern Mexican state of Oaxaca. Wikipedia

Nea Moni of Chios.label: Nea Moni of Chios
Nea Moni of Chios.description: Nea Moni is an 11th-century monastery on the island of Chios that has been recognized as a UNESCO World Heritage Site. It is located on the Provateio Oros Mt. in the island's interior, about 15 km from Chios town. Wikipedia

Mukden Palace.label: Mukden Palace
Mukden Palace.description:
The Mukden Palace or Shenyang Gugong, also known as the Shenyang Imperial Palace, is the former imperial palace of the early Qing Dynasty of China.
It was built in 1625 and the first three Qing emperors lived there from 1625 to 1644. Wikipedia

Nesvizh Castle.label: Nesvizh Castle
Nesvizh Castle.description: Nesvizh Castle or Niasvizh Castle is a residential castle of the Radziwiłł family in Nesvizh, Belarus. Wikipedia

Newgrange.label: Newgrange
Newgrange.description: Newgrange is a prehistoric monument in County Meath, Ireland, about one kilometre north of the River Boyne. It was built about 3200 BC, during the Neolithic period, which makes it older than Stonehenge and the Egyptian pyramids. Wikipedia

Omo River.label: Omo River
Omo River.description: The Omo River is an important river of southern Ethiopia. Its course is entirely contained within the boundaries of Ethiopia, and empties into Lake Turkana on the border with Kenya. Wikipedia

Palace of the Shirvanshahs.label: Palace of the Shirvanshahs
Palace of the Shirvanshahs.description: Palace of the Shirvanshahs is the biggest monument of the Shirvan-Absheron branch of the Azerbaijan architecture, situated in the Inner City of Baku. Wikipedia

Palace of Tau.label: Palace of Tau
Palace of Tau.description: The Palace of Tau in Reims, France, was the palace of the Archbishop of Reims. It is associated with the Kings of France, whose coronation was held in the nearby cathedral of Notre-Dame de Reims. Wikipedia

Pannonhalma Archabbey.label: Pannonhalma Archabbey
Pannonhalma Archabbey.description: The Benedictine Pannonhalma Archabbey or Territorial Abbey of Pannonhalma is the most notable landmark in Pannonhalma and one of the oldest historical monuments in Hungary, founded in 996. It is located near the town, on top of a hill. Wikipedia

Old City (Jerusalem).label: Old City
Old City (Jerusalem).description: The Old City is a 0.9 square kilometers walled area within the modern city of Jerusalem. Until 1860, when the Jewish neighborhood Mishkenot Sha'ananim was established, this area constituted the entire city of Jerusalem. Wikipedia

Portobelo, Colón.label: Portobelo, Colón
Portobelo, Colón.description: Portobelo is a port city in Colón Province, Panama, established during the Spanish colonial period. Wikipedia

Prambanan.label: Prambanan
Prambanan.description: Candi Prambanan or Candi Rara Jonggrang is a 9th-century Hindu temple compound in Central Java, Indonesia, dedicated to the Trimurti, the expression of God as the Creator, the Preserver and the Destroyer. Wikipedia

Qal'at al-Bahrain.label: Qal'at al-Bahrain
Qal'at al-Bahrain.description: The Qal'at al-Bahrain, also known as the Bahrain Fort or Fort of Bahrain and previously as the Portugal Fort is an archaeological site located in Bahrain, on the Arabian Peninsula. Wikipedia

Rock Paintings of Sierra de San Francisc.label: Rock Paintings of Sierra de San Francisco
Rock Paintings of Sierra de San Francisc.description: The Rock Paintings of Sierra de San Francisco is the name of the prehistoric rock art pictographs found in the Sierra de San Francisco mountain range in Mulegé Municipality of the northern region of Baja California Sur state, in Mexico. Wikipedia

Ring of Brodgar.label: Ring of Brodgar
Ring of Brodgar.description: The Ring of Brodgar is a Neolithic henge and stone circle on the Mainland, the largest island in Orkney, Scotland. It is part of the UNESCO World Heritage Site known as the Heart of Neolithic Orkney Wikipedia

Sammallahdenmäki.label: Sammallahdenmäki
Sammallahdenmäki.description: Sammallahdenmäki is a Bronze age burial site in Finland in Lappi municipality. It was designated by UNESCO as a World Heritage Site in 1999, and includes 36 granite burial cairns dating back more than 3,000 years, to 1,500 to 500 BC. Wikipedia

Safranbolu.label: Safranbolu
Safranbolu.description: Safranbolu is a town and district of Karabük Province in the Black Sea region of Turkey. It is about 200 kilometres north of Ankara and about a 100 km south of the Black Sea coast, or more precisely about 9 km north of the city of Karabük. Wikipedia

Seokguram.label: Seokguram
Seokguram.description: The Seokguram Grotto is a hermitage and part of the Bulguksa temple complex. It lies four kilometers east of the temple on Mt. Tohamsan, in Gyeongju, South Korea. Wikipedia

Seri Bahlol.label: Seri Bahlol
Seri Bahlol.description: Seri Bahlol is located near Takht Bhai, about 70 kilometres north-west of Peshawar, Khyber Pakhtoonkhwa, Pakistan. Wikipedia

San Leucio.label: San Leucio
San Leucio.description: San Leucio is a frazione of the comune of Caserta, in the region of Campania in southern Italy. It is most notable for a resort developed around an old silk factory, included in the UNESCO World Heritage sites list in 1997. Wikipedia

Shark Bay.label: Shark Bay
Shark Bay.description: Shark Bay is a World Heritage Site in the Gascoyne region of Western Australia. It is an area centred approximately on 25°30′S 113°30′E﻿ / ﻿25.500°S 113.500°E, 800 kilometres north of Perth, on the westernmost point of Australia. Wikipedia

Shirakami-Sanchi.label: Shirakami-Sanchi
Shirakami-Sanchi.description: Shirakami-Sanchi is a UNESCO World Heritage Site in northern Honshu, Japan. This mountainous, unspoiled expanse of virgin forest straddles both Akita and Aomori Prefectures. Wikipedia

South China Karst.label: South China Karst
South China Karst.description: The South China Karst, a UNESCO World Heritage Site since June 2007, spans the provinces of Guangxi, Guizhou, and Yunnan. It is noted for its karst features and landscapes as well as rich biodiversity. Wikipedia

St. Procopius Basilica in Třebíč.label: St. Procopius Basilica in Třebíč
St. Procopius Basilica in Třebíč.description: St. Procopius Basilica is a Romanesque-Gothic Christian church in Třebíč, Czech Republic. It was built on the site of the original Virgin Mary's Chapel of the Benedictine monastery in 1240–1280. Wikipedia

Sian Ka'an.label: Sian Ka'an
Sian Ka'an.description: Sian Ka'an is a biosphere reserve in the municipality of Tulum in the Mexican state of Quintana Roo. It was established in 1986 and became a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1987. Wikipedia

Su Nuraxi di Barumini.label: Su Nuraxi di Barumini
Su Nuraxi di Barumini.description: Su Nuraxi is a nuragic archaeological site in Barumini, Sardinia, Italy. It was inscribed on the UNESCO list of World Heritage Sites in 1997 as Su Nuraxi di Barumini. Wikipedia

Tripitaka Koreana.label: Tripitaka Koreana
Tripitaka Koreana.description: The Tripitaka Koreana or Palman Daejanggyeong is a Korean collection of the Tripitaka, carved onto 81,258 wooden printing blocks in the 13th century. Wikipedia

Summer Palace.label: Summer Palace
Summer Palace.description: The Summer Palace is a vast ensemble of lakes, gardens and palaces in Beijing, China. The Summer Palace is mainly dominated by Longevity Hill and the Kunming Lake. It covers an expanse of 2.9 square kilometres, three-quarters of which is water. Wikipedia

Three Parallel Rivers of Yunnan Protecte.label: Three Parallel Rivers of Yunnan Protected Areas
Three Parallel Rivers of Yunnan Protecte.description: The Three Parallel Rivers of Yunnan Protected Areas is a UNESCO World Heritage Site in Yunnan province, China. Wikipedia

Wieliczka Salt Mine.label: Wieliczka Salt Mine
Wieliczka Salt Mine.description: The Wieliczka Salt Mine, located in the town of Wieliczka in southern Poland, lies within the Kraków metropolitan area. Wikipedia

Wooden churches of the Slovak Carpathian.label: Wooden churches of the Slovak Carpathians
Wooden churches of the Slovak Carpathian.description: Carpathian Wooden Churches is the name of a UNESCO World Heritage Site that consists of nine wooden religious buildings constructed between the 16th and 18th centuries in eight different locations in Slovakia. Wikipedia

Viñales Valley.label: Viñales Valley
Viñales Valley.description: Viñales Valley is a karstic depression in Cuba. The valley has an area of 132 km² and is located in the Sierra de los Órganos mountains, just north of Viñalesm in the Pinar del Río Province. Wikipedia

Wudang Mountains.label: Wudang Mountains
Wudang Mountains.description: The Wudang Mountains consist of a small mountain range in the northwestern part of Hubei Province of China, just to the south of the city of Shiyan. Wikipedia

Xochimilco.label: Xochimilco
Xochimilco.description: Xochimilco was the most important city of the Xochimilca people, one of the Nahua tribes that migrated to the Mesoamerica region. The city was founded around 900 AD. Wikipedia

Xochicalco.label: Xochicalco
Xochicalco.description: Xochicalco is a pre-Columbian archaeological site in the Municipality of Miacatlán in the western part of the Mexican state of Morelos. The name Xochicalco may be translated from Nahuatl as "in the house of Flowers". Wikipedia

Woodhenge.label: Woodhenge
Woodhenge.description: Woodhenge is a Neolithic Class II henge and timber circle monument located in the Stonehenge World Heritage Site in Wiltshire, England. It is 2 miles north-east of Stonehenge in the parish of Durrington, just north of Amesbury. Wikipedia

Yakushima.label: Yakushima
Yakushima.description: Yakushima, is one of the Ōsumi Islands belonging to Kagoshima Prefecture, Japan. The island, 504.88 km² in area, has a population of 13,178. Access to the island is by hydrofoil ferry, slow car ferry, or by air to Yakushima Airport. Wikipedia

Yungang Grottoes.label: Yungang Grottoes
Yungang Grottoes.description: The Yungang Grottoes are ancient Chinese Buddhist temple grottoes near the city of Datong in the province of Shanxi. They are excellent examples of rock-cut architecture and one of the three most famous ancient Buddhist sculptural sites of China. Wikipedia

Abbey of Fontenay.label: Abbey of Fontenay
Abbey of Fontenay.description: The Abbey of Fontenay is a former Cistercian abbey located in the commune of Marmagne, near Montbard, in the département of Côte-d'Or in France. It was founded by Saint Bernard of Clairvaux in 1118, and built in the Romanesque style. Wikipedia

Aqueduct of Segovia.label: Aqueduct of Segovia
Aqueduct of Segovia.description: The Aqueduct of Segovia is a Roman aqueduct and one of the most significant and best-preserved ancient monuments left on the Iberian Peninsula. Wikipedia

Batalha Monastery.label: Batalha Monastery
Batalha Monastery.description: The Monastery of Batalha, literally the Monastery of the Battle, is a Dominican convent in the civil parish of Batalha, in the district of Leiria, in central region of Portugal. Wikipedia

Burgos Cathedral.label: Burgos Cathedral
Burgos Cathedral.description: Burgos Cathedral is a Gothic-style Roman Catholic cathedral in Burgos, Spain. It is dedicated to the Virgin Mary and is famous for its vast size and unique architecture. Wikipedia

Chan Chan.label: Chan Chan
Chan Chan.description: The largest Pre-Columbian city in South America, Chan Chan is an archaeological site in the Peruvian region of La Libertad, five km west of Trujillo. Wikipedia

Congonhas.label: Congonhas-São Paulo Airport
Congonhas.description: São Paulo/Congonhas Airport is one of the three commercial airports serving São Paulo, Brazil. The airport is named after the neighborhood where it is located, formerly called Vila Congonhas, property ... Wikipedia

Cueva de las Manos.label: Cueva de las Manos
Cueva de las Manos.description: Cueva de las Manos is a cave or a series of caves located in the province of Santa Cruz, Argentina, 163 km south of the town of Perito Moreno. It is famous for the paintings of hands. The art in the cave dates from 13,000 to 9,000 years ago. Wikipedia

Fatehpur Sikri.label: Fatehpur Sikri
Fatehpur Sikri.description: Fatehpur Sikri is a city and a municipal board in Agra district in the state of Uttar Pradesh, India. The city was founded in 1569 by the Mughal emperor Akbar, and served as the capital of the Mughal Empire from 1571 to 1585. Wikipedia

Dolomites.label: Dolomites
Dolomites.description: The Dolomites are a mountain range located in northeastern Italy. They form a part of Southern Limestone Alps and extend from the River Adige in the west to the Piave Valley in the east. Wikipedia

Emas National Park.label: Emas National Park
Emas National Park.description: The Emas National Park is a national park and a UNESCO World Heritage Site in the states of Goiás and Mato Grosso do Sul in Brazil. Wikipedia

Generalife.label: Generalife
Generalife.description: The Palacio de Generalife was the summer palace and country estate of the Nasrid Emirs of the Emirate of Granada in Al-Andalus, now beside the city of Granada in the autonomous community of Andalusia, Spain. Wikipedia
